      "writtenOn": "2019-01-14T21:02:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think it could be both things. The old clear-as-draw shaders were very stripped down, and direct GLSL while the new shader goes through the full SkSL transformation (so even once it\u0027s cached, there will be some overhead here). The op creation could be a mixed bag; it may help in some cases due to batching, but in general the rect op is larger than the clear op and has more logic in it.\n\nI will do some local tests to see numbers.",
      "parentUuid": "7407ec65_2504023c",
